title: A Coalition that is left of centre ‘cannot win’ an election
description: Former NSW treasurer Michael Costa claims that a Coalition that is left of centre “cannot win” an election.  “The real issue here is a Coalition that is left of centre cannot win an election,” Mr Costa told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.   “They need to clean out the policy problems, get their values right, and focus where they have to focus, and that is outer suburban seats in the regions.”

title: China top official threatens investment withdrawal over Labor election promise
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond analyses how the Chinese regime is threatening trade withdrawals over Labor’s promise to take back the Port of Darwin.

title: ‘Designed to scare people’: Climate change concerns continuously growing
description: The Australian’s Environment Editor Graham Lloyd says the continuous talking about climate change is “designed to scare people”.

title: ‘More turmoil’: National Party to face spill motion on return to parliament
description: Sky News host Peta Credlin says there is more turmoil inside the former Coalition as the National Party is likely to face a spill motion on the return of parliament next week.  “More turmoil today inside the former Coalition, with the Nationals' leader David Littleproud likely to face a spill motion when parliament returns next week,” Ms Credlin said.  “If the party in Canberra, and around the country, can't lift its game, it's gone. It is that serious.”

title: Russia continues targeting Ukraine’s energy infrastructure as winter takes hold in region
description: Ukraine reports more than 700,000 people are without power in Kyiv, during one of the coldest winters to date.   Russia appears to be taking advantage of temperatures as low as minus 20 degrees to target energy infrastructure, directly affecting residents in their homes.

title: Labor government ‘captive’ to majority Muslim Western Sydney branches
description: Former Victorian Liberal Party president Michael Kroger says Labor is “captive” to their branches in Western Sydney that are majority Muslim.    “Labor is a captive to their branches in Western Sydney,” Mr Kroger told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “They certainly have an unprecedented amount of influence on this Labor government.”

title: Labor’s out-of-control spending is ‘unacceptable’
description: Former Liberal candidate for Bennelong Scott Yung discusses the Labor government’s out-of-control spending, describing it as “unacceptable”.   “I think this is the single biggest issue facing Australians right now,” Mr Yung told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “That’s quite unacceptable, for young Australians especially wanting to buy their own home.”

title: ‘Idiotic’: Basketball Australia blasted for ‘foolish’ Australia Day statement
description: Broadcaster Dee Dee Dunleavy blasts Basketball Australia for their “idiotic” statement posted about Australia Day.  “It’s foolish, in fact, I would go so far as to say it’s idiotic to put this post up because as we’ve seen with the polls … the overwhelming majority of Australians support celebrating Australia Day on January the 26th,” Ms Dunleavy told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “To post this, you’re immediately alienating a large part of your fanbase who do not agree with you.  “They would have served themselves better to have posted something that engendered love of country and pride in Australia.  “I just think this post was dumb and they obviously were trying to appear morally superior to the rest of us.”

title: ‘They should be grateful’: Pay push for ball kids at Australian Open dismissed
description: Broadcaster Dee Dee Dunleavy weighs in on the debate surrounding the push for remuneration for Australian Open ball kids.   “It’s voluntary, they’re choosing to do it, they’ve got the best seat in the house for some of the finest tennis in the world,” Ms Dunleavy told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “No one is making them do it … it’s great on their CV.  “I think they should be grateful that they’re getting this opportunity, and I reckon if you ask the kids, they would say they are perfectly happy to be doing it for nothing.”

title: Brooklyn and Nicola will ‘never win’ the feud with Victoria and David
description: Broadcaster Dee Dee Dunleavy claims Brooklyn Beckham and Nicola Peltz will “never win” the feud with Victoria and David Beckham.  “Brooklyn and Nicola Peltz are never going to win this battle against Posh and Becks,” Ms Dunleavy told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “Let’s be honest, we wouldn’t have known who Brooklyn was unless he was a Beckham; he is nothing without his parents' name.  “Nicola and Brooklyn, who really, as far as I can see, have not contributed anything to this world.”

title: ‘Crybaby’ tennis star throws massive tantrum after humiliating Australian Open loss
description: Broadcaster Dee Dee Dunleavy blasts tennis star Coco Gauff, calling her a “crybaby” after she was seen having a meltdown following her Australian Open loss.  “None of us, I think, expects privacy anywhere that we go and not just the famous,” Ms Dunleavy told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “She wants to blame the cameras; the only person she has to blame is herself.  “She threw a tantrum because she lost … we don’t need to build some place where they can go and be a crybaby.”

title: Expert comments on Scott Morrison’s plea to Muslim leaders
description: Former Victorian Liberal Party president Michael Kroger says the Western world has a problem with radical Islam.   “I think there’s a lot of truth in what Scott Morrison has said,” Mr Kroger told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “We’ve vilified a million gun owners for the actions of two … we have a problem with radical Islam in Australia and the Western world.”

title: Tennis star cries about peace in America despite embarrassing meltdown
description: Broadcaster Dee Dee Dunleavy urges tennis player Coco Gauff to show “restraint” after she smashed her racquet following her Australian Open loss.  “A few days ago, in her post-match interview, she said that she hopes for peace in her country, which is America,” Ms Dunleavy told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “And yet, her actions are exactly the opposite; that wasn’t very peaceful action at all.  “In the privacy of her own home, she can do whatever she likes, but I think in public, have a bit of restraint.”

title: Sky News poll reveals how ‘competitive’ One Nation would be if election held today
description: Sky News Chief Election Analyst Tom Connell breaks down the numbers in the Sky News Pulse polling data.  “This won’t be every single seat, but this is an indication of just how competitive they’re going to be,” Mr Connell told Sky News host Peta Credlin.  “If an election were to be held, of course, today.”

title: Sky News Pulse: One Nation surge continues at pace
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray discusses inflation, Islamic extremism, US politics and more.
